Stay Safe Online Checklist (Prevention Tips)
- General Cyber Safety Tips
	1.	Never share OTP, passwords, or PIN with anyone.
	2.	Always check website URLs before entering personal details.
	3.	Do not click on unknown or suspicious links.
	4.	Install apps only from trusted sources like Play Store/App Store.
	5.	Keep phone and apps updated regularly.
	6.	Use strong passwords and change them regularly.
  
- UPI / Financial Safety Tips
	7.	Never approve unknown “Collect Request” in UPI apps.
	8.	Remember: Receiving money does NOT require entering a PIN.
	9.	Avoid using public Wi-Fi for online payments.
	10.	Enable SMS and app transaction alerts.

- Reporting Cybercrime

If cyber fraud happens, report immediately:
	•	National Cyber Crime Portal:  https://www.cybercrime.gov.in
	•	Cybercrime Helpline Number: 1930
